==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Frond
<hw>Frond</hw> <pr>(fr⟦ocr⟧nd)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>frons</ets>, <ets>frondis</ets>, a leafy branch, foliage.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The organ formed by the combination or union into
one body of stem and leaf, and often bearing the fructification; <as>as,
the <ex>frond</ex> of a fern or of a lichen or seaweed</as>; also, the
peculiar leaf of a palm tree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Frondation</ent>⟦br⟧
